					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/robert-voor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1378159); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1378159&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183384" alt="Robert Voor" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1378159)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/robert-voor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1378159); return false;" >Robert Voor</a></span> <span class="odate time_1496024412 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 May 2017 02:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2835514">
									

<p><em>Capture of all members should be done non-lethally. Standard person of interest interview protocol should be followed, with members then amnesticized as needed and released.</em></p>
<p>Is this standard operating procedure for a threat level Yellow GoI? Multiple members of this group could be classified as SCPs themselves, in particular Jude who's a full-on reality bender. I don't understand why the Foundation is doing 'catch and release' here. Which leads me to a question: In-universe, would a group like GAW land on the GOC's radar, and might they take a more 'proactive' approach to dealing with this GoI than the Foundation would?</p>

							</div>

								
					
