					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183384" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;" >Decibelles</a></span> <span class="odate time_1496025013 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 May 2017 02:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2835521">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Is this standard operating procedure for a threat level Yellow GoI?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd imagine so.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Multiple members of this group could be classified as SCPs themselves, in particular Jude who's a full-on reality bender. I don't understand why the Foundation is doing 'catch and release' here.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Because, in my view, the Foundation killing people (even skips) without needing to is cruel and fucked up, especially when said people have hard enough lives as-is. Sure, Jude could be contained and classified as an SCP himself; the Foundation may have considered that and may even adopt that as their plan in the future (AKA, after this dossier was created). But JJ could manage to use his luck to break him out maybe. And even aside from that; it's not exciting narratively.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>In-universe, would a group like GAW land on the GOC's radar, and might they take a more 'proactive' approach to dealing with this GoI than the Foundation would?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Possibly? At the moment, I don't think GAW is landing on the GOC's radar in a way to make them want to devote resources to hunt these people down, especially if they're hard to track to begin with.</p>

							</div>

								
					
