					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183384" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;" >Communism will win</a></span> <span class="odate time_1496025715 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 May 2017 02:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2835537">
									

<p>I imagined that, being a coalition of occult organizations to begin with, the GOC probably wants to, y'know, talk with them to see whether they're worth bringing into the fold. If the answer is &quot;absolutely not&quot;, <em>then</em> they could probably start escalating.</p>
<p>I also envisioned the main reason the Foundation doesn't just start locking GAW members up being that it could bring on retaliation from the rest of the group. They're quasi-manageable as-is, but what if they got really pissed and started cranking out things with the express purpose of being hard to contain? Nobody wants that.</p>
<p>The events of my own GAW series, incidentally, being the ones that probably informally established this relationship.</p>

