				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1918720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183384" alt="Scorpion451" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1918720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;" >Scorpion451</a></span> <span class="odate time_1496030574 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 May 2017 04:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2835624">
									

<p>Personally, I headcanon a lot of realpolitik in the Foundations dealings with people like Jude; on the one hand ideally they would like him to not be running around being a reality bender. On the other, he's really not doing much actual <em>harm</em>, and they've got people trying to unleash Elder Things upon the world and only so many squads of highly trained operatives.</p>
<p>Basically, its the difference between trying to catch Banksy for vandalism and trying to catch a serial killer. Even if they caught Banksy, would anyone really press charges, or would they just give him a stern talking to about filing for permits?</p>

							</div>

								
